Author: far33d
Content:
The interesting point here is that the new IE release had no effect on Firefox adoption - it only affected the IE6 numbers. Personally, I find this somewhat surprising, but also more interesting than the fact that firefox now has a narrow lead (for a site with a tech audience).

Once users go to Firefox, they don't go back to IE. It's a one way street.
